"insertions":9,"deletions":0}}},{"hash":"6a72104242252c39ef4a233c0950baef7eb20d00","isMergeCommit":true,"messageTitle":"Merge pull request #22 from podledges/Ayden-AboutUs","messageBody":"Added Ayden.md and added Ayden to AboutUs.md","fileTypesAndContributionMap":{}},{"hash":"a5423f2ab6e31e5ea10c372d007da5f3339287a9","isMergeCommit":false,"messageTitle":"Implement batch command, organize Ui printing and Codebase","messageBody":"The application currently lacks a way to add and track specific\nbatches of inventory items. Additionally, print statements are\nscattered across different classes, and the centralized parsing\nlogic will become harder to manage as we add more features.\n\nIntroducing the batch feature requires a solid foundation for\nparsing its specific parameters. At the same time, moving output\nhandling strictly to the Ui class ensures a clean separation of\nconcerns, making the code much easier to read and maintain.\n\nLet\u0027s,\n* implement BatchCommand to handle adding batches with expiry dates\n* update InventoryItem to track batchQuantity and getQuantity\n* migrate scattered print statements into dedicated Ui class methods\n* extract prepareBatchCommand and prepareCreateCommand in Parser\n* update the Command interface to accept Ui and Inventory parameters\n* implement the exit command and resolve the early exit bug\n* extract helper functions from the main loop in the MediStock class\n\nCentralizing output in the Ui class keeps our logic decoupled from\nuser presentation. Structuring the batch implementation this way,\nalong with the updated Command interface, provides a highly modular\ntemplate for any future commands we add.\n","fileTypesAndContributionMap":{"functional-code":{"insertions":242,"deletions":35}}},{"hash":"b603de328f680fb8337096436f14b440da02da36","isMergeCommit":true,"messageTitle":"Merge remote-tracking branch \u0027upstream/master\u0027 into feature/batch","messageBody":"","fileTypesAndContributionMap":{}},{"hash":"640b1a2ca22b